I don&#39;t think passing the whole component is a good practice, if viable at all. A recommended practice would just be passing functions to the child component as props, like such:

    class Comp1 extends React.Component&lt;...,...&gt; {
    
      doSomething () {
        // some code
      }

      doAnotherThing() {
        // more code
      }

      render() {
        return ( 
          &lt;Comp2 
            doSomething={this.doSomething} 
            doSomethingElse={this.doAnotherThing}
          /&gt; 
        )
      }
    }

You can read more about this pattern in the [official docs][1].


  [1]: https://reactjs.org/docs/lifting-state-up.html

